      <Placemark>
        <name>Majda</name>
        <description><![CDATA["It feels like an alternate universe..." Tony says of this restaurant run by a couple, where the husband is Muslim and the wife is Jewish. He ate fried eggs with peppers from the garden; roasted tomatoes, okra, onions, and mint; grilled zucchini covered in fried yogurt sauce; fresh zucchini with mint and tiny sweet apricots]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-9C27B0</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            35.116514,31.790605,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Gaza</name>
        <description>Tony had a meal with Laila El-Haddad and her family. They ate maqluba (a traditional Palestinian dish made of layers of fried eggplant, tomato, potatoes, caramelized onions, and chicken, sautéed then simmered in a broth with nutmeg, cinnamon, cardamom, and rice). They traveled just outside Gaza City to a gathering place for elders where they had fatit ’ajir (roasted baby watermelon, eggplant, tomatoes, squash, chiles, and olive oil) served with unleavened bread.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-9C27B0</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            34.4668445,31.5016951,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>מידס‎</name>
        <description>Tony spoke with the owner of this restaurant whose daughter was killed. They discussed both sides of the conflict.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-0288D1</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            34.6433069,31.5566924,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Bar Aliatar Los Caracoles</name>
        <description>Tony and his Director of Photography Zach Zamboni (who lives part time in Andalucia with his wife), ate a lunch of snails in almond sauce at this eatery with seating outdoors.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
