          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Bar Gallardo</name>
        <description>Bar #3 for the group. They ate cheese, fried smelts, picarones (fried pastry), chulatitas (baby lamb chops). </description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -3.6084444,37.1778611,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Beach barbecue</name>
        <description>Tony went to a moraga (a beach barbecue)  with chefs Juan Andres Moria and Rafael Luca, and friends. They had dried tuna on toast with spicy olive oil, fish, cheese, pate, grilled octopus, sea bream, pork tenderloin, and morcilla (blood sausage).</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-9C27B0</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -2.4637136,36.834047,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Casa Pasteles Albayzin</name>
        <description>Cafe con leche and a small breakfast like toast with tomato.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1534-795548</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -3.5935149,37.1826871,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Meal with locals</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Zach's wife's family invited Tony for dinner. Iberico ham, remojon granadino (eaten during holy week, it has salt cod, egg, black olives, oranges, and tomatoes dressed in olive oil), migas (sardines, chorizo, melons, and peppers)]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1603-9C27B0</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -3.5985571,37.1773363,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
