      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[John's Hotdog Deli]]></name>
        <description>Tony had the deluxe: sausage made with bacon and garlic, homemade mustard, onions pickled in beer.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1810-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            12.5657987,55.6730621,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Monaci delle Terre Nere</name>
        <description>Agri tourismo - a working farm, hotel, restaurant. Produces olive oil. On his last day in Sicily, he had a meal here made from ingredients on the farm: penne with sundried tomatoes and zucchini; a rabbit dish; agridolce greens</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1602-7CB342</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            15.1078125,37.6727749,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Spiaggia libera di Isola Bella</name>
        <description><![CDATA[The beach where they launched the boat to go "fishing" and then dropped dead fish, octopus, and shellfish into the water around Tony. He described his feelings on this experience saying he slid "quickly into a spiral of near hysterical depression." After this scene he gets really drunk.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1861-FF5252</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            15.3004132,37.8528716,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Osteria Nero d'Avola]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony had dinner here after the disastrous "fishing" expedition. It's his birthday and he doesn't remember any of the meal because he drank so much. Tomaso and his wife (locals) had the meal together. They ate white olives, bread, olive oil, abalone served raw in the shell, baby sardines called neonata with citrus and salt, octopus, tuna tartare, cuttlefish crudo, pasta alfino querta (a true Sicilian classic made with fennel, pine nuts, saffron, and anchovy. Served with anchovy curing in chestnuts and salt for days, then lightly fried in oil.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1573-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            15.2835386,37.8504554,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Trattoria Piccolo Napoli</name>
        <description>Tony met with food writer Mary Taylor Simeti, food writer, for lunch. They had panelli (fritter made from chickpeas), caponata (sweet and sour eggplant), spaghetti al nero di seppia (spaghetti in cuttlefish ink), casarecce al pescespada (pasta with swordfish, eggplant, and tomatoes)</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            13.3584805,38.1274755,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[D'Antone]]></name>
        <description>Tony tried horse meat here. They grilled it outside on the street. Tony enjoyed it.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            15.0796141,37.5075716,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Parco dei Nebrodi</name>
        <description>Tony went to a free range pig farm located in this national park. They cooked one of them, using the lungs and liver in a stew with garlic, chili pepper, red wine. They also make blood sausage and serve it with homemade cured meats, local cheese, and homemade wine.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1566-FF5252</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            14.7061826,37.9328644,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Catania Market</name>
        <description>Very old market selling meats, produce, cheese, and other local goods. The market is best known for its seafood.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1578-673AB7</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            15.0885311,37.5092633,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Meal with locals</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony had dinner at Tomaso's mother's home. They had caponata; bread and tomato salad; shrimp sautéed in garlic, butter, and herbs; sardines fillet sautéed in garlic, oil, and red pepper]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1603-9C27B0</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            15.0830304,37.5078772,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Soweto</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony watched a soccer game at Mawilies Inn (could not find on the map) in Soweto, a suburb of Johannesburg. The town name derives from an abbreviation of Southwestern Township. They ate lamb's head; mieliepap (sticky porridge made from maize); stewed beef, dumplings, stewed greens, carrots, beans, gravy.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1696-0288D1</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            27.8540323,-26.2485377,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>The Yeoville Dinner Club</name>
        <description>Chef Sanza cooked for Tony: A Nigerian dish of egusi and beef (cooked with melon and pumpkin seeds) futu (crumbly cornmeal porridge); basmati rice with rose water; achar (pickled eggplant and mango); Congolese cassava; and falafel. Menu changes daily.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            28.06764,-26.18147,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
