          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Toshima City</name>
        <description>There used to be a boxing gym in Toshima called Yurakura Gym, but I could not find it on the map.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1761-BDBDBD</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            139.7168209,35.7262664,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Yasuda</name>
        <description>Tony loves Yasuda in NYC, and wanted to find out why the chef, whom the restaurant is named for, would suddenly move back to Tokyo. Yasuda said that Japan is the origin of sushi, so he wanted to return to where it was created. Yasuda is also a karate master.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            139.7204488,35.6659319,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Daitoryo</name>
        <description>Tony meets with Tamika (a professional dominatrix; Kinoko Hajime, a shibari (Japanese form of rope bondage) artist and Tamika’s partner; and Naga, a translator also joined) at this Izakaya restaurant. They have Kusaia, which is grilled fermented fish, yakitori, and motsunabe (intestine stew with miso).</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            139.7748694,35.7103644,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Mienoumi</name>
        <description>Tony had a meal with Toshio Maeda, the manga illustrator credited with inventing tentacle porn. They ate katsuo no tataki (seared bonito with daikon, fresh greens, sprouts, and ponzu) and tomato nabe (a hot pot of meat and vegetables favored by sumo wrestlers).</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            139.7975462,35.6721022,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Mahakala</name>
        <description>Tony had a meal with Chef Yasuda, they had kushiage (fried skewers of shrimp and basil, lotus fruit, octopus, and quail eggs) and okonomiyaki (egg-batter pancake stuffed with squid). Yasuda lives near here and loves this place.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            139.6972358,35.6469063,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Packard Automotive Plant</name>
        <description>Tony visited Al Hill, who lives on the site of the 3.5 million sq ft auto plant that is no longer in use.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1523-0288D1</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -83.028669,42.3794008,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Duly's Place Coney Island]]></name>
        <description>This place has been around for over 90 years. Open 24 hours. The Coney dog has chili, cheese, onions, and mustard atop a hot dog.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1810-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -83.1017346,42.3179685,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Cutters Bar & Grill]]></name>
        <description>Tony met with Adolph Mongo, a political strategist, and had a vodka.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1517-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -83.03769,42.3483856,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>The Heidelberg Project</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tyree Guyton created this "delightfully loony outdoor community art project that began in 1986 and now attracts 35,000 visitors per year from around the world." ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1523-FF5252</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -83.0208429,42.3586679,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>MT. Elliott Charlevoix Market</name>
        <description>Tony visited this liquor store to pick up some alcohol.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1578-FF5252</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -83.018527,42.3570299,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Greedy Greg's Soul Food]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[A backyard BBQ serving soul food. Tony had smoked pork loaded collards and mac & cheese. ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -82.975302,42.427253,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Engine 23 Squad 3</name>
        <description>Tony visited this fire department to eat with the firefighters. They made crabcakes, broccoli salad, and steak.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-673AB7</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -83.0363067,42.3755257,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>1301 Broadway St</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Former site of Guns & Butter, where Tony ate with Charlie Leduff, a journalist,  at a pop-up restaurant with Chef Craig Lieckfelt.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-BDBDBD</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -83.0458079,42.3345569,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Pupuseria Y Restaurante Salvadoreno</name>
        <description>Home cooked Salvadoran meals. Tony ate here with Chef George Azar and friend Joe. They had tamales, pupusas, and shrimp with garlic butter.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -83.1165258,42.3247796,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
    </Folder>
    <Folder>
      <name>Season 3</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Pritam Dhaba</name>
        <description><![CDATA["Get used to eating a lot of vegetarian. India is one of the few places on Earth where, even for me, that's not a burden," Tony says. He had chickpeas, saag, and lots of naan.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            74.8679822,31.6346306,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Golden Temple</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony called this the "Sikh equivalent of the Vatican." He attended a festival called a gurpurab where feet are cleansed and people of all religions all take part in a simple meal]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1678-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            74.8764741,31.6199625,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>All India Famous Amritsari Kulcha</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Iconic dish of Punjab. "A perfect little flavor bomb of wheat dough pressed against the side of a very, very hot clay oven, slathered with butter and served with a chickpea curry on the side."]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            74.8695061,31.6496751,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Beera Chicken House</name>
        <description>Tony had tandoori chicken and fresh baked naan</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            74.8842231,31.6424865,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Tea Stall And Snacks Stall</name>
        <description>Tony had some snacks at this train station on his way to the Himalayas.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            77.0824093,30.8900032,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Shimla</name>
        <description><![CDATA["Here the colonials created England in miniature," Tony says of this hill town.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1523-0288D1</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            77.1734033,31.1048145,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Chapslee</name>
        <description>Tony stayed at this place where a maharaja once lived. He ate some of the food such as mulligatawny soup.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1602-7CB342</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            77.1789638,31.108946,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Bootlegger Italian Bistro</name>
        <description><![CDATA[A locals' joint with live entertainment. ]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1517-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -115.1716636,36.0492651,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Raku</name>
        <description>Japanese Izakaya that is fancy and pricy, but casual. Tony met with Penn Jillette and ate sea urchin, tuna, Japanese river crab, hasaki sashimi, hasaki belly, juicy deep-fried chicken, hamachi belly, and fish collar</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -115.2098191,36.1270386,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Marquee Nightclub & Dayclub]]></name>
        <description>Tony met with EDM DJ Jason Lima to talk about Vegas nightlife, which he admitted he is too old to understand.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1637-FF5252</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -115.174224,36.1094505,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Oscar's Steakhouse]]></name>
        <description>Tony met with former mayor and mob lawyer, Oscar Goodman.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -115.146565,36.171779,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>eat.</name>
        <description>Tony had a meal with artist Anthony Bondi at this breakfast and lunch spot.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -115.1389775,36.1668996,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Lotus of Siam</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony ate here with Chef Jet Tila, who said this place has the "best Thai food in Vegas by far." You MUST have northern Thai food here. Tony says DO NOT order the pad thai. They had nam prik (a composed room temperature salad); nam kao tod (a puffed crispy rice salad with preserved pork sausage); hung lay (pork curry braised with garlic and ginger); and Northern larb.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -115.143203,36.1436042,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>é by José Andrés</name>
        <description>Tony ate Iberico ham and bean soup with roasted garlic; nitro almond cup, a frozen shell made from a puree of Marcona almonds, filled with almond milk espuma and finished with Andalusian caviar; mussels, olives with an escabeche “air;” truffle egg, a gelee of truffles formed into an egg shape with an actual yolk suspended in the center; crispy chicken skin escabeche; salt-roasted foie gras and clementine sauce; secreto de cerdo en papillote.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -115.1753911,36.1099462,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Huntridge Tavern</name>
        <description>Dive bar where Tony drank some Jameson Black</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1517-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -115.137866,36.158234,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Reynon</name>
        <description>Tony ate sabodet (sausage made from pig’s head, tongue, and beef) with Chef Georges Reynon and Chef Daniel Boulud.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            4.8342779,45.7594697,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[L'Institut Restaurant]]></name>
        <description><![CDATA[One of the nation's greatest culinary schools, started by Paul Bocuse. Tony and Daniel Boulud tried the poulet en vessie (chicken cooked inside a pig’s bladder).]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-FF5252</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            4.8331785,45.7562485,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Saint-Pierre-de-Chandieu</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony visited Chef Boulud's childhood school in this town, where Chef Boulud explained the fresh, healthy meals students are given here. They had pumpkin soup, fish with couscous, cheese with chocolate and orange segments.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1682-FF5252</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            5.010241,45.644571,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Café Comptoir Abel</name>
        <description>Tony ate here with Chef Boulud and Bill Buford, a former fiction editor at The New Yorker. They had quenelle de brochet en gratin maison (gratin dumplings)</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            4.8258415,45.7540443,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Bouchon Comptoir Brunet</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Bill Buford called this "a very male tradition," called the Franc Machon. They ate Blanquette de Veau (slowly stewed neck and shoulder of veal with mushrooms served over rice); bread, Beaujolais wine.]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            4.837644,45.763943,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Troisgros</name>
        <description>Chefs Michel and Cesar Troisgros carry on the family tradition of nouvelle cuisine. Tony had salmon in sorrel sauce, a dish that he says changed the world.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            3.9919448,46.0096964,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Paul Bocuse Restaurant</name>
        <description>Tony said it had always been his dream to eat here. Paul Bocuse is considered the father of modern French cuisine. They ate soupe aux truffes noires V.G.E. (black-truffle soup named after former French President Valéry Giscard d’Estaing); loup en croûte feuilletée (sea bass in pastry crust); choron (béarnaise or hollandaise sauce made with tomato purée); pot-au-feu (French beef stew); lièvre à la royale (roasted hare).</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            4.847408,45.815668,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Escuela de Box Rudy Perez</name>
        <description>Tony visited this boxing gym to speak with boxer Jorge Lacierva</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1761-0288D1</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -99.2601053,19.3949616,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>MIGAS La Guera</name>
        <description>Located in a large public market in the neighborhood of Tepito, which is known to be a rough area to live in. Tony and hosts had migas: Cracked ham bones stewed with garlic, onion, cascabel chiles, and epazote; thickened with stale bread and served with tortillas.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -99.1279774,19.4465066,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Máximo Bistrot</name>
        <description><![CDATA[Tony ate in Chef Eduardo Garcia's kitchen at this restaurant, one of the hottest places in Mexico. He ate abalone with chiles, lemon, and brown butter; confit of suckling pig, "topped with grandma’s salsa and served on a tortilla."]]></description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -99.1580296,19.4188421,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Monte Albán</name>
        <description>The Zapotec ruins are here. Tony and his guide drank mescal here.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1523-0288D1</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -96.7674673,17.0454573,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Central de Abastos Oaxaca</name>
        <description>Chef Alejandro Ruiz Olmedo and Tony visited this Central Market where they ate barbacoa tacos, consommé, and tlayudas (perhaps best described as a Oaxacan pizza).</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-673AB7</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -96.7334671,17.0581054,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Restaurante Tlamanalli</name>
        <description>Tony visited a small town called Teotitlán del Valle and met Abigail Mendoza, a descendant from pre-Spanish Mexicans. She cooked a Chicken mole for him, using 35 kinds of chiles. The dish takes 2 weeks to prepare. She also made cow and pork brains cooked with chiles, tomatoes, and yerba santa.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -96.521176,17.0291229,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Espacio Zapata</name>
        <description>Tony spoke with street artist Yescka about revolutionary art.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1509-FF5252</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -96.7257473,17.0665466,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Cantina El Danubio</name>
        <description>Tony had drinks with poet and activist Javier Sicilia.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1517-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -99.2374286,18.9270578,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Metropol Hotel</name>
        <description>Tony met up with Zamir and ate Astrakhan caviar, salted cucumber with honey, Baltic sprat with beetroot, muksun (white fish with maldon salt), and vodka (of course)</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            37.6216236,55.7583798,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Yornik (Closed)</name>
        <description>Tony and Zamir had a meal with Boris Nemtsov, one of the main critics of Putin, who served as an advisor under Yeltsin (he has since been assassinated in 2015, and this restaurant is now closed).</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-BDBDBD</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            37.5862504,55.7738616,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Meal with locals</name>
        <description>Tony met with Alexander Lebedev, businessman and owner of opposition newspaper Novaya Gazeta, at his home. They had fresh potato chips and Scottish salmon with cherry-tree sawdust.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1603-9C27B0</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            37.4280579,55.740653,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>16 Tonn</name>
        <description>Tony had drinks with Travis Link, manager of punk rock band Louna, and Rouben Kazariyan</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1517-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            37.5643644,55.7643119,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Kazansky railway station</name>
        <description>Tony and Zamir took the luxury Grand Express train from Moscow to St. Petersburg. Aboard the train, they had blini with caviar and cold pickled herring, and vodka.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1716-0F9D58</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            37.6567589,55.7736033,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>The Loft Club (Closed)</name>
        <description>Tony met with Xena Robrek, an openly gay artist and filmmaker, and Darya Tarasova, a local fixer and translator at this club to have drinks.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1879-BDBDBD</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            30.3557051,59.9219072,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Cococo (Closed)</name>
        <description>Former site of restaurant called Cococo. Tony and Zamir had a meal with Sergey Shnurov and Matilda Shnurova, co-owners of Cococo.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-BDBDBD</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            30.3087591,59.9349492,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Petropavlovskaya Krepost']]></name>
        <description>Former site of a fortress built to protect the city from marauding Swedes, it was taken over by Bolshevik rebels.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1523-0288D1</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            30.3166668,59.95,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Big Apple Inn</name>
        <description>Tony ate smokes (smoked-sausage sandwich) and ears (pig’s ear sandwiches), both served with housemade hot sauce and coleslaw; hot tamales.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -90.1886799,32.3051111,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Soul Wired Cafe</name>
        <description>Tony met with Pyinfamous, a local hip hop artist, to have drinks.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1517-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -90.17603,32.355036,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Quapaw Canoe Company</name>
        <description>Tony went on a canoe tour on the Mississippi River.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1536-FF5252</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -90.575758,34.20117,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name>Buck Island</name>
        <description>Tony and the canoe guide stopped here to cook food on a fire.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-FF5252</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -91.450116,31.269338,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Doe's Eat Place]]></name>
        <description>Opened in 1941. Tony had a Delta dinner of Doe’s famous salad, hot tamales, fries, shrimp, and porterhouse steaks.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -91.0561567,33.4156348,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[The Senator's Place]]></name>
        <description>Tony ate classic Southern soul-food buffet of collard greens, fried okra, mac ’n’ cheese, lima beans, red beans, neck bones, rice and gravy, a piece of fried chicken.</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>
            -90.7173402,33.7296239,0
          </coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
