      <Placemark>
        <name><![CDATA[Ethel's Grill]]></name>
        <description>Tony went to this small eatery with 2 chefs, Andrew Lay and Mark “Gooch” Noguchi. They ate miso soup, pigs feet soup, tripe, taco rice (taco toppings and an over-easy egg on top of rice, which is an Okinawan specialty).</description>
        <styleUrl>#icon-1577-C2185B</styleUrl>
